[Early 1990s]

4
00:01:03,160 --> 00:01:04,280
Has Ma Rulong arrived yet?

5
00:01:04,600 --> 00:01:05,400
Not yet.

6
00:01:05,800 --> 00:01:06,280
Ms. Shao.

7
00:01:06,680 --> 00:01:07,640
Would you like to take a short break?

8
00:01:28,120 --> 00:01:28,760
Youngest.

9
00:01:29,000 --> 00:01:30,080
Is dad awake yet?

10
00:01:30,640 --> 00:01:31,440
Not yet.

11
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,760
Dad trusted Ma Rulong most.

12
00:01:34,760 --> 00:01:35,880
But he's not here.

13
00:01:38,240 --> 00:01:39,920
He's the Acting Chair now.

14
00:01:40,200 --> 00:01:41,640
Outranks us all.

15
00:01:43,280 --> 00:01:44,360
He has to come last.

16
00:02:02,960 --> 00:02:03,760
Chairman.

17
00:02:11,600 --> 00:02:12,920
Let me think about it.

18
00:02:14,600 --> 00:02:15,680
Is something wrong with the Chairman?

19
00:02:15,680 --> 00:02:17,280
Got us trapped here now.

20
00:02:45,160 --> 00:02:45,720
Ma Rulong.

21
00:02:45,960 --> 00:02:46,680
The old man is in critical condition.

22
00:02:46,920 --> 00:02:47,840
You locked us in here.

23
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:48,640
What are you trying to do?

24
00:02:51,400 --> 00:02:52,200
Ma Rulong.

25
00:02:53,080 --> 00:02:55,120
No one at the Welfare Home
taught you manners, huh?

26
00:02:56,400 --> 00:02:57,280
My dad,

27
00:02:57,360 --> 00:02:59,080
and all these uncles here,

28
00:02:59,520 --> 00:03:00,880
they all followed Old Shao
back in the day,

29
00:03:00,880 --> 00:03:02,640
starting from nothing together.

30
00:03:03,560 --> 00:03:04,800
Who do you think you are?

31
00:03:05,480 --> 00:03:07,680
What gives you the right to sit here?

32
00:03:08,080 --> 00:03:09,080
Do you really think,

33
00:03:09,280 --> 00:03:11,480
being an adopted son
makes you real family?

34
00:03:12,040 --> 00:03:12,560
You,

35
00:03:13,200 --> 00:03:14,680
go back to where you belong.

36
00:03:15,520 --> 00:03:16,320
Mr. Yuan.

37
00:03:18,920 --> 00:03:20,160
Are you even a man?

38
00:03:20,160 --> 00:03:21,320
You dared touch my woman.

39
00:03:22,680 --> 00:03:25,040
The whole project scam is out now.

40
00:03:25,120 --> 00:03:26,520
He knows everything about it.

41
00:03:40,880 --> 00:03:42,320
All present are veterans.

42
00:03:42,600 --> 00:03:43,320
The old man

43
00:03:43,320 --> 00:03:44,160
is out of respect for the past.

44
00:03:45,080 --> 00:03:46,480
The shady money you took...

45
00:03:47,320 --> 00:03:48,160
Let's just let that go.

46
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:50,880
Next, I'm taking over.

47
00:03:51,280 --> 00:03:53,000
I have one simple request.

48
00:03:53,800 --> 00:03:55,400
Your shares in hand,

49
00:03:55,840 --> 00:03:56,800
all of them must be handed over.

50
00:03:57,840 --> 00:03:59,320
If you don't, it's easy.

51
00:04:02,280 --> 00:04:03,880
You'll make the front page tomorrow.

52
00:04:11,720 --> 00:04:13,080
I'm backing Ma Rulong.

53
00:04:13,400 --> 00:04:14,600
I'll sign right here.

54
00:04:14,640 --> 00:04:15,680
I support Ma Rulong too.

55
00:04:15,760 --> 00:04:16,320
Count my signature in.

56
00:04:16,520 --> 00:04:17,360
I'm in support as well.

57
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:18,200
Me too.

58
00:04:19,040 --> 00:04:20,200
I'm with Ma Rulong too.

59
00:04:20,280 --> 00:04:20,960
I'll sign, too.

60
00:04:21,600 --> 00:04:22,280
I'm in as well.

61
00:04:22,520 --> 00:04:23,040
Count me in.

62
00:04:23,080 --> 00:04:23,640
I'm also on board.

63
00:04:23,640 --> 00:04:24,160
I'll sign too.

64
00:04:31,880 --> 00:04:32,680
Alright then.

65
00:04:36,120 --> 00:04:38,160
Didn't expect you had it in you.

66
00:04:39,840 --> 00:04:41,000
Remember this.

67
00:04:42,040 --> 00:04:43,240
We're not done yet.

68
00:04:43,840 --> 00:04:45,000
Just you wait.

69
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,880
The old man is gone.

70
00:05:09,520 --> 00:05:10,960
Got it.

71
00:05:33,440 --> 00:05:34,800
Mr. Ma, what are you looking for?

72
00:05:37,200 --> 00:05:37,800
Where's the lighter?

73
00:05:38,320 --> 00:05:39,000
The lighter?

74
00:05:39,240 --> 00:05:40,800
Isn't it in your hand?

75
00:05:43,080 --> 00:05:43,400
Here you go.

76
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:43,960
Mr. Ma.

77
00:05:44,240 --> 00:05:45,000
Take it easy.

78
00:05:54,080 --> 00:05:54,680
Go to the hospital.

79
00:05:54,840 --> 00:05:55,440
Okay.

80
00:06:50,520 --> 00:06:51,240
Long.

81
00:06:51,320 --> 00:06:52,160
Go.

82
00:07:43,840 --> 00:07:45,080
I'm short one.

83
00:08:36,960 --> 00:08:37,400
Oh no.

84
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:38,480
Oh no.

85
00:08:38,800 --> 00:08:39,680
Sorry, really sorry.

86
00:08:39,840 --> 00:08:40,840
Here, let me help you.

87
00:08:40,920 --> 00:08:41,640
Let's head to the hospital.

88
00:08:42,200 --> 00:08:42,680
I'll take you there.

89
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:46,880
I'm not going to the hospital.

90
00:08:47,280 --> 00:08:48,280
That won't work.

91
00:08:48,280 --> 00:08:48,680
Trust me.

92
00:08:48,840 --> 00:08:49,240
Come on.

93
00:08:49,240 --> 00:08:50,040
I'm begging you.

94
00:08:53,160 --> 00:08:53,960
I'm not going to the hospital.

95
00:08:54,600 --> 00:08:55,320
Why not?

96
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:56,920
If not the hospital, then where?

97
00:08:59,360 --> 00:09:00,320
Your place.

98
00:09:03,640 --> 00:09:04,440
What?

99
00:09:05,680 --> 00:09:06,480
What is it?

100
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,760
Any news from the people
looking for my big brother?

101
00:09:21,840 --> 00:09:22,800
No updates yet.

102
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:27,520
The Old Immortal showed up in my dream.

103
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:29,440
Said my big brother is still alive.

104
00:09:30,920 --> 00:09:32,760
Don't waste our money.

105
00:09:33,240 --> 00:09:34,440
Keep searching.

106
00:09:35,440 --> 00:09:37,800
We need him found, dead or alive.

107
00:09:43,520 --> 00:09:44,960
[Hongmeng Fashion]

108
00:09:45,680 --> 00:09:47,000
Once you're awake, get going.

109
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:48,960
Don't try to trick me.

110
00:10:11,560 --> 00:10:12,600
Who is he even...

111
00:10:12,920 --> 00:10:14,320
Wearing shoes that thin?

112
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:29,080
Oh my god.

113
00:10:31,720 --> 00:10:32,520
Locking the door?

114
00:10:33,000 --> 00:10:34,080
Are you mad?

115
00:10:34,280 --> 00:10:35,160
Let me lock it for you.

116
00:10:35,840 --> 00:10:36,640
Come on.

117
00:10:43,040 --> 00:10:43,840
Let's talk inside.

118
00:10:44,320 --> 00:10:45,440
What are you doing?

119
00:10:53,400 --> 00:10:54,640
Why don't we sit?

120
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:02,640
What's this about?

121
00:11:03,040 --> 00:11:04,040
It's late.

122
00:11:04,120 --> 00:11:05,840
You already know why I'm here.

123
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:08,120
I, O...

124
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,480
And U.

125
00:11:10,200 --> 00:11:11,320
The IOU.

126
00:11:11,560 --> 00:11:12,960
I only borrowed ten grand.

127
00:11:13,320 --> 00:11:15,120
With interest, it's over twenty now.

128
00:11:15,120 --> 00:11:16,600
I've paid it all back.

129
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:17,760
If you keep this up,

130
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:19,560
who'd ever borrow from you again?

131
00:11:21,760 --> 00:11:23,160
You put your fingerprint on it, right?

132
00:11:23,480 --> 00:11:25,320
Technically, that IOU belongs to me now.

133
00:11:25,320 --> 00:11:26,120
Don't you even know?

134
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:30,200
You borrow money, you pay it back.

135
00:11:30,360 --> 00:11:31,320
That's just how it works.

136
00:11:31,640 --> 00:11:32,480
Don't make this hard for me.

137
00:11:32,600 --> 00:11:33,800
I'm just collecting for someone else.

138
00:11:34,360 --> 00:11:35,000
Are you paying or not?

139
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:36,280
I'm not paying you back.

140
00:11:36,800 --> 00:11:37,200
Get up.

141
00:11:37,320 --> 00:11:38,000
Move it, now.

142
00:11:40,000 --> 00:11:41,560
What do you want?

143
00:11:42,160 --> 00:11:43,080
Are you kidding me?

144
00:11:43,200 --> 00:11:44,240
Fine, don't pay.

145
00:11:45,360 --> 00:11:46,240
Pay another way.

146
00:11:48,960 --> 00:11:50,360
Did you drink before this?

147
00:11:51,080 --> 00:11:52,200
Don't push me.

148
00:11:52,320 --> 00:11:52,840
Get out.

149
00:11:54,320 --> 00:11:55,120
Come on.

150
00:11:55,760 --> 00:11:56,640
Let's talk inside.

151
00:11:56,640 --> 00:11:57,160
Don't, Huzi.

152
00:11:57,280 --> 00:11:57,840
Take a seat...

153
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:04,280
What is that?

154
00:12:04,360 --> 00:12:05,680
I didn't see it, bro.

155
00:12:29,320 --> 00:12:30,280
Can you see it now?

156
00:12:36,800 --> 00:12:38,480
Who even are you?

157
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:55,800
Don't mess with me.

158
00:12:56,600 --> 00:12:57,440
Do you know me or not?

159
00:12:57,560 --> 00:12:58,240
San Hu.

160
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,440
My big brother is Mad Huang.

161
00:13:04,960 --> 00:13:06,040
Bet you're scared now.

162
00:13:12,400 --> 00:13:14,080
If you can't hear, I'm done talking.

163
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:18,360
Alright then.

164
00:13:18,440 --> 00:13:19,480
You hired bodyguards now?

165
00:13:23,480 --> 00:13:24,280
Well, umâ€¦

166
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:26,240
Why are you locking it?

167
00:13:27,920 --> 00:13:28,720
Hurry, run!

168
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:39,800
Bro.

169
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:41,960
Bro, don't look at me. I'm scared.

170
00:14:02,840 --> 00:14:03,640
Who...

171
00:14:05,040 --> 00:14:05,880
am I?

172
00:14:09,440 --> 00:14:11,040
You don't know who you are,

173
00:14:11,480 --> 00:14:12,040
right?

